<title xml:lang="en">Support to the National Program on the Response to HIV Epicemic in the Republic of Armenia</title>
<description type="1">While Armenia is still a country with a concentrated HIV epidemic, it has seen a substantial growth of identified HIV cases over the past six years, partially due to increased voluntary counseling and testing services. This program implemented by the Ministry of Health aims to accelerate the reduction of the HIV epidemic in the country by providing antiretroviral treatment for those who need it, universal access to counseling and testing among pregnant women and general population, HIV prevention activities among prisoners and mobile populations, methadone substitution treatment, HIV education in school settings, strengthening of national information, monitoring and evaluation, laboratory and procurement and supply management systems.</description>
